{
  "stem": "942.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were two of them, two brothers, the two Lichman brothers that are alive today-- one is living in Los Angeles, and one is living in Long Island, New York.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember so vividly that at the end of the [NON-ENGLISH], which is the end of the particular season, which was in the summer when our school year finished, the Hebrew school, and there were exams.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And these two fellows and a few others, they were able to tell many pages of the Talmud, you know, without-- just by heart.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was always amazed at this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I was sort of learning all my years till about the age of 12.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All this was sort of hammered in year after year, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was like a, a repetition type of thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I really didn't understand much of what I was learning until I came back from the concentration camp, where I had to learn German.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then I understood sort of, you know, what I learned in the Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Understanding, the [HEBREW], which is the five books of Moses-- Genesis, Exodus, and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the first thing that you started to learn in Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then there was the commentaries on that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we also learned [HEBREW], which is Talmud.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this was-- life went on pretty good.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I used to-- I remember we had-- my friends, as we were coming out of school every day, we used to go by the baker, whose name was Mr.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Deutsch.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember he was a tall man, and he always had a long pipe with a long stem, and he was always smoking this pipe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went into his bakery and picked it up little kaisers.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
